        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "%lld",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 30,
          "startingLine": 737
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "When enabled, the app watches the iCloud Drive > Up Next root and imports audio files from there when you open the iCloud Drive view. Turning it off stops discovery, but keeps existing sideloaded items in the database.",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 18,
          "startingLine": 824
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "Supported formats include MP3, AAC, M4A, M4B, WAV, CAF, AIFF, and any other audio type AVFoundation can open.",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 18,
          "startingLine": 828
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "Setting up the iCloud folder...",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 30,
          "startingLine": 833
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "Enable Sideloading",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 23,
          "startingLine": 820
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "Rebuilding analytics…",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 26,
          "startingLine": 1061
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "Remove Duplicate Podcasts",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 20,
          "startingLine": 1132
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "App Icon",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 26,
          "startingLine": 1446
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "Using Up Next",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 26,
          "startingLine": 1665
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "Up Next Basics",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 21,
          "startingLine": 1634
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "Queue Behavior",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 21,
          "startingLine": 1640
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "Chapter Skip Keywords",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 21,
          "startingLine": 1646
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "Siri & Shortcuts Intents",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 21,
          "startingLine": 1652
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "Accessibility",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 21,
          "startingLine": 1658
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "Up Next is your single playback queue. Episodes in this list are what the player uses for \"what comes next.\"",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 22,
          "startingLine": 1635
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "Inbox is your triage area for fresh episodes. Move important ones into Up Next or archive what you do not want to keep visible.",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 22,
          "startingLine": 1636
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "When an episode finishes, continuous playback can automatically start the next item from Up Next.",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 22,
          "startingLine": 1637
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "New episodes can be placed at the front, end, or not added automatically, depending on your settings.",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 22,
          "startingLine": 1641
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "The currently playing episode is kept pinned at the top while playback is active.",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 22,
          "startingLine": 1642
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "You can reorder Up Next manually, move an episode to the end, or remove episodes from the queue.",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 22,
          "startingLine": 1643
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "Chapter rules let you skip recurring segments like intro, ads, or outro.",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 22,
          "startingLine": 1647
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "Rules are checked against chapter titles and can use operators like contains, starts with, or ends with.",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 22,
          "startingLine": 1648
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "Use global rules for all podcasts, or enable custom settings for one podcast when it needs its own behavior.",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 22,
          "startingLine": 1649
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "Available actions now include: Resume Playback, Pause Playback, Bookmark This, Skip Forward, Skip Backward, Play Up Next, Play Next Up Next Episode, Move Current To End, Remove Current From Up Next, Refresh Podcasts, and Generate Podcast Share Image.",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 22,
          "startingLine": 1653
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "In Apple Shortcuts, search for Up Next to add these actions to personal automations.",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 22,
          "startingLine": 1654
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "For best results, keep a few Siri phrases short and specific, like \"Play Up Next\" or \"Bookmark this in Up Next.\"",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 22,
          "startingLine": 1655
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "VoiceOver and Voice Control use the same control names you see in the player, queue, and transcript views.",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 22,
          "startingLine": 1659
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "For captions, open Transcript from an episode or the player. When a feed has no transcript, you can generate one on-device.",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 22,
          "startingLine": 1660
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "Reduced Motion, Larger Text, and Differentiate Without Color are supported. If you use high contrast settings, the app increases secondary text contrast in now-playing interfaces.",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 22,
          "startingLine": 1661
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "Shortcuts",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 26,
          "startingLine": 1724
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "Automatic Backgrounds",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 21,
          "startingLine": 1713
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "Useful Outputs",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 21,
          "startingLine": 1718
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "Up Next actions are available in Apple Shortcuts. Search for “Up Next” when adding an action to a shortcut or personal automation.",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 22,
          "startingLine": 1676
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "Open Shortcuts",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 27,
          "startingLine": 1679
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "Apple Shortcuts",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 22,
          "startingLine": 1682
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "Automatic for Period picks the background from the data period, not from the day the shortcut runs. A shortcut running on 1 June with Previous Period uses May’s background.",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 22,
          "startingLine": 1714
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "For yearly images, Automatic for Period uses the New Year background. For day, week, and month images, it uses the month containing the listening history.",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 22,
          "startingLine": 1715
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "Generate Podcast Share Image returns a PNG file. Shortcuts can pass that file to Save File, Save to Photo Album, Messages, Mail, or Share Sheet.",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 22,
          "startingLine": 1719
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "To create multiple designs, add the Generate Podcast Share Image action more than once with different design values.",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 22,
          "startingLine": 1720
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
        "key": "%lld",
        "location": {
          "startingColumn": 18,
          "startingLine": 1768
        }
      },
      {
        "comment": "",
